Photo: VCGDisney's live-action "Aladdin" topped the Chinese mainland box office for a third day on Sunday after its Friday debut, the China Movie Data Information Network said Monday. The film pulled in around 48.89 million yuan (about 7.09 million US dollars) on the day, accounting for about 44 percent of the daily total. It was followed by live-action/animated film "Pokemon Detective Pikachu," which brought in 19.14 million yuan. Coming in the third was Universal Picture's "A Dog's Journey," which earned 12.65 million yuan. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star